 to the forcing of Earth's\norbital evolution. Our results illustrate how small changes to the architecture\nof a given planetary system can result in marked changes in the potential\nhabitability of the planets therein, and are an important first step in\ndeveloping a means by which the nature of climate variability on planets beyond\nour Solar System can be characterised.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 11 Aug 2017 06:43:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-08-14"}
